# Working with ggplot themes

---

## Using ready-made themes

::: {.small-font}


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(penguins, aes(flipper_length_mm, body_mass_g, color = species)) +
  geom_point()
  # default theme is theme_gray()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![&nbsp;](figure-design_files/figure-revealjs/penguins-complete-themes-1.svg){width=60%}
:::
:::


:::


## Customizing theme elements

::: {.tiny-font}


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(penguins) +
  aes(flipper_length_mm, body_mass_g) +
  geom_point(aes(color = species)) +
  theme_minimal_grid()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![&nbsp;](figure-design_files/figure-revealjs/penguins-theme-elements1-1.svg){width=100%}
:::
:::


:::

## Customizing theme elements

::: {.tiny-font}


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(penguins) +
  aes(flipper_length_mm, body_mass_g) +
  geom_point(aes(color = species)) +
  theme_minimal_grid() +
  theme(
    # change overall font family
    # (requires font to be available)
    text = element_text(
      family = "Comic Sans MS"
    )
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![&nbsp;](figure-design_files/figure-revealjs/penguins-theme-elements2-1.svg){width=100%}
:::
:::


:::

## Customizing theme elements

::: {.tiny-font}


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(penguins) +
  aes(flipper_length_mm, body_mass_g) +
  geom_point(aes(color = species)) +
  theme_minimal_grid() +
  theme(
    # change color of axis titles
    axis.title = element_text(
      color = "royalblue2"
    )
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![&nbsp;](figure-design_files/figure-revealjs/penguins-theme-elements3-1.svg){width=100%}
